# Docker and Containerization Standards

- Follow Docker best practices for image building
- Use multi-stage builds to minimize image size
- Use specific base image versions rather than 'latest'
- Include only necessary files in Docker context
- Properly handle permissions in containers
- Implement proper health checks for services
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Implement proper logging from containers
- Ensure proper error handling in entrypoint scripts
- Optimize Docker layer caching
- Implement proper cleanup of temporary files
- Set appropriate resource limits for containers
- Use Docker Compose for local development orchestration
- Follow consistent naming conventions for services
- Implement proper security practices for containers